caption: Best restaurant our Superior Curves Boutique modeing group visited while in town from Havelock, NC!  Great customer service and the food was spectacular.  Our server was the owner and he was very attentive. If you are ever in Brooklyn, NY, don't hesitate to visit. You will not be disappointed 😁😁😁😁

This place is always fun. The drinks are ofd the chains here. There are few options for vegans/ vegetarians but i did manage to get a few. The staff is very nice , friendly and accommodating. The place is clean and comfortable . Definitely will be back!!
Great cocktails, friendly staff, decent prices.
Awesome!!

I went on my first date with my girlfriend here 3.5 years ago. While that would warrant five stars by itself, Blueprint is a wonderful bar in a city with countless amazing bars. The atmosphere is incredible. The drinks are reasonably priced, and the selection is great. Bathrooms are clean. The food is amazing too!

Our go-to neighborhood bar for celebrating birthdays, new gigs, leases, the end of hard work days. Always such attentive, thoughtful service. Cocktails (seasonal and their house ones) are superb—complex, delicious, and properly stiff. Bar bites are equally high quality—the house-cured salmon, watermelon feta salad (in summer), duck BLT, and shishito peppers are our faves. Looking forward to trying their latest warm holiday cocktail. Rooting hard for Blueprint to survive the winter months!
Amazing drinks and charcuterie!
Great cocktails, but you have to wait to get a table

The cocktails are top notch and the food is great too. Perfect place for a light dinner and a chat with friends. The backyard is lovely. There are socially distanced tables in the backyard and out front.
Best cocktails in park slope!
Great cocktails and wine - everyone got something that was perfect for them. Bartender happy to spend time letting you taste wine or finding out exactly what you're looking for
good food good cocktails, portions are alittle small but very good quality
Great place for a craft cocktail even in abnormal times. Kudos to the staff for their artistry and care.
Favorite local cocktail bar. Currently open until 11 with outdoor seating.
Very nice place with delicious cocktails
Clarified chai milk punch! Yes please, nice drinks, great service
Great cocktails, wide whiskey selection, delish food, warm atmosphere, cute patio
Good spot try the artichokes on a Sunday!
Yum
Really good drinks, good service, and nice setting. No wonder it’s hard to get a table.
Simply the best cocktails in the neighborhood.

Came here after driving up from Philly. Cocktails were delicious (I had the Vieux Carre...well, two, actually). Food-wise, we got the rabbit pot pie, baby octopus, pork butt sliders, and Brussels sprouts and bacon pizza. Everything was excellent, and the portions were pretty generous as well. Would highly recommend to anyone in the area.
Delicious cocktails. Fun music
I've been there multiple times & the service is always on point. I would recommend to anyone who is hanging around the Barclay's that wants to dive into the 5th ave bars
Excellent cocktail and super friendly staff!
food was  great.
Really great spirit-forward cocktails, really delicious small plates, cute backyard. My favorite cocktail bar in the area by far.

Great bar with great drinks and great food. We got the anchovies and the chicken liver mousse, both very delicious. The rabbit stew was great, while their pizza was a bit too heavy on the dough and cheese side. All in all a great place and the staff are knowledgeable and attentive. Will definitely come again.
I love when the employees share the enthusiasm of the patrons. Bring greeted with a smile makes this place all the better

I love a good cocktail bar and Blueprint doesnt dissapoint. There's a lot of places that make rack drinks and call it a cocktail but Blueprint is several steps above. If you're looking for a nice place to chat with friends or date this is the perfect place. Dim lighting, small bites and great selection of cocktails
Great drinks. Food looked great. Prices mid to high. Friendly staff!
Best cocktails in the neighborhood.
Ok place for a drink.  Food is underwhelming.
Great spot for cocktails, and non alcoholic spirits, too. This is a date spot with a cozy ambiance. They have decent food in a tapas style for sharing.
Great cocktails and small plates. Good first date spot or casual night out.
Fantastic drinks! Great atmosphere. Super friendly staff.
(Translated by Google) Cocktails and aperitifs, Italian inspired food  (Original) Cocktail e aperitivi, il cibo italian inspired
Phenomenal drinks 🙌🏼

I came in with my family to get some tasty meats and cheeses and was not disappointed. The seasonal cocktails really complimented the menu. Stayed longer than expected and would highly recommend if you are in the neighborhood 👍intimate atmosphere

Yummy cocktails.  Cheese and meat plate is lovely. The cheeses were really good and 3 different kinds.  Toasts were good as well.  Crunchy bread that is perfect for cheese.  Nice ambiance too, except for some babies screaming in the back... Well, parents need a cocktail for sure to keep sain and restart fresh at being a parent as soon as they get home.  So that was fine by me.
have only been once but had really great cocktails and charcuterie. i've been meaning to go back!!
(Translated by Google) Excellent drinks attention and atmosphere.  (Original) Excelentes tragos atención y ambiente.

They make great cocktails and have decent plates. Service can be on the slower side if you're on the patio and a bit apathetic. But the patio is quiet and cute and it's a good place to grab and drink and just relax.
Great cocktails but when I went it was super dark and really hot inside
Great cocktails and surprisingly deliscious food
Nice bar, cute space, great drinks...I should have led with that
Nice cocktail lounge with high end drinks and bartenders that know how to make them!
Absolutely fantastic. Dinner, drinks, dessert. Drinks are creative and terrific. A must-try.
I've been multiple times now. Love the ambiance, drinks, plates, and staff! The owner's dog and I share the same name...so we worked together to create a drink named after us!
Cocktails and food plates made for a great after-show spot for an old, married-with-kids couple.
Great cocktails and bites

Fantastic cocktails, favorite is the vieux carre. Service is very attentive and quick. Does get very busy, but not packed; usually seating service only. Great setting for a date. They're really great at what they do, which is a nice cocktail bar, without the gimmicks or pretences of some of the "speakeasies" you can find.
Excellent food and drink.
Fantastic cocktails and tasty bite. I had the Continental Divide coctail and the bourbon flourless cake. The cocktail was great but the cake was better!
Delicious food, great service and staff.
Awesome cocktails and a chill vibe, a great spot for post shift drinks!

Fantastic atmosphere, fantastic cocktails and delicious tapas style food. I had the Marksman cocktail and am willing to come back to Brooklyn to have it again. We didn't feel rushed despite the busyness, and even had a nice chat with our waitress. I would definitely recommend this place!
Just cruising through you know the deal
Relaxed atmosphere, friendly staff, good people
Great cocktails and food.  Lovely place and service.
I enjoy the choices in a pinch. The staff is usually nice & willing to help you with any issues.
Great people, beautiful place.

I thought this was a great spot, super interesting drink menu, you can definitely order something you’ve never had before here. Servers are friendly and quick, space is large enough for a bigger group but still intimate enough for a date night.
Really great cocktail bar with interesting drinks. The food is amazing too!
Great place to hang out, delicious cocktails! 😍
Great place to get a refreshing cocktail
Know what? For a real nothing of a place this is a pretty great place. Interesting menu, reasonably priced drinks, friendly staff. It's LOUD,  bit that's sort of  ok. Great find!
The cocktails aren’t the best and a little over priced. But a nice bar. The food is small portioned and not good. I would not recommend eating here but maybe grabbing a quick drink is fine.

Dropped in to Blueprint by fluke but loved my experience. I checked off a bucket list classic cocktail off my list and they played Rage Against The Machine. What more can you ask for? Try the Last Word, Kentucky Tanlines and My Dear Julius!
Seriously amazing cocktails.
A great neighborhood bar. Staff is friendly. And they serve food til 2am.

Cozy place for after work drinks. Service is only at the bar. There's a second floor loft that oversees the main floor. This floor would be best for larger groups. Otherwise there are small tables and bar space in the main level. Good selection of wine, but vast selection of spirits and butters for cocktails. Ambiance is warm with a urban rustic vibe. Very centrally located especially if you work close to trans bay terminal.
I like this place. Always a good time. Drinks are tastefully done, ambiance is perf. Manny is great, too. :)
Delicious. Thanks all you need to know.
Best cocktail spot in the area, great vibe for small groups and food is great accompaniment to some amazing drinks.

This is the perfect spot to catch up with a friend you haven't seen in a while.  Or to wrap up a second or third date in.  It has couches by a fire, a cozy ambiance that is quiet enough to talk but lively enough that it doesn't feel sedated.  The drinks are well priced, and the bartenders are always super friendly.
Nice late night place
On pointe
Bartender had a little mishap at our table but was really kind about it and offered to comp our drink. Will be coming back!
Good cocktails.
Brilliant cocktails in a warm, inviting atmosphere. The backyard is wonderful when the weather cooperates.
The drinks were excellent and the wait staff were prompt and nice.
Fantastic cocktails and great small plates to share with that special "some" one.
Not a shabby menu, had cocktails and dessert. Bread pudding and flourless chocolate bourbon cake were excellent. The set up is kind of crammed, no AC?
Very good juices
The roasted brussels sprouts are SO good!
Best gin fizz I had in a long time. Very cute and cozy bar.
Really nice bartenders, helped me get my umbrella back
Great place.

Beautiful selection of intricate cocktail recipes, good food (and I'm a foodie), and great atmosphere. Lovely porch in the back. Our new favorite spot! We're slowly working our way through every cocktail on the menu. Love it!

Decent date spot because its generally fast service and quaint. I'm giving it 3 stars because I once walked in on a Friday night and while I was waiting for my entire party to arrive I found a roach hanging out on the wall. We decided not to stay that night.

By far the best cocktail bars in park slope. I’ve always have been greeted by the bar staff when I walk in, just letting you know that they see you when it’s a wait to order a drink. All the cocktails are measured and use great ingredients. All the bartenders are friendly and knowledgeable and water is refilled regularly. Music is pretty good too.
It was an awesome experience! The service, the food, everything was wonderful! We really enjoyed the boquerones and the ham from North Carolina is so good (and we are from Spain!)
Best cocktails in Brooklyn. Ask for something similar to an espresso martini, bartender came up with a great concoction.
Amazing place to eat and service is great

Really enjoy this place; The bartenders are very laid back and attentive (Shout out to Jerry!) and are willing to go in depth on their creations.  The food is fun, cultured and filling.  The lighting is perfect.  For the quality of service, food, drinks and location, this place is a solid value.  Highly recommended.  I still can't get over the marble brick that flows around the place.  Enjoy!
Best mixology bar in town. Great ambience and the food is good.  There is street parking. All staff was friendly...last thing prices won't break your bank. 😊
Great menu and cocktails
The doctors in is the best drink ever. It's the one floating around with an orchid in a sea of gun.  The absinthe isnt offensive and although flavorful  every part of the drink is harmonized.
The staff was friendly and offered good recommendations.  They served us an awesome cheese plate at 1:45am!
great food
Very nice spot to have a drink with your date
Priced high, but such is park slope. A small but nice back yard and a dim interior.
Good food
Decent Mezcal selection, good cheese selection, that's all I ask for.
Great Vibe, dim-lit and pretty good drinks!
Cozy, classy spot for freshly prepared cocktail and light bites. Hidden gem in neighborhood!

They use quality ingredients in their drinks and have a solid menu of cocktails. They'll make you something off menu based on your tastes. The food is delicious and for the most part healthy - great for weekend mid  afternoon drinks & eats. Their interior and back patio are comfortable . Friendly staff as well :)
We had lovely craft cocktails and friendly staff on the back patio. 😍
Fantastic service...laid back but attentive. Really feels like a neighborhood spot, only with fantastic fancy cocktails. Great for dates.
Excellent drinks. Great platers too.
Try the kickstarter. They also make a great penicillin. Great cocktails and food.
They make a killer old fashioned and have a lovely staff.
A cozy bar with great cocktails and bartenders.

Simply the best cocktails I've ever had anywhere. They turn drink making into a true art form. And their food menu is along the same line as far as quality goes. An amazing place to settle down for an evening of relaxing and sipping on some of the most delicious beverages anyone could think of.
Friendly staff and strong, in cocktails. Can get a bit hot and crowded on weekend nights but the rear nook is nice.
Great backyard!

Late post, but this i such a great place to hangout and get great food and some delicious drinks. I had their long island ice tea which is one of the best i have ever had. I also had their baby octopus which was amazing.

You walk in, it looks like a typical pub. But it isn't. Cocktails are made with care and the food is a notch above solid -- certainly better than it has to be considering that it's primarily a bar, and the kitchen is open late to boot.
Great cocktails.
Good drinks menu.  Nice place to sit with a date and have a cocktail.  Good small plates.

Best cocktails in the neighborhood, friendly and knowledgeable bartenders. It's good for small plates before going elsewhere, but I wouldn't eat a meal here. Prices are a little steep, but I do enjoy coming here.
Great drink options
Great cocktails and the duck club is killer.
Cocktails and share plates. All recipes are unique to Blueprint.
Excellent cocktail bar. Probably the best one in the area. A little pricey.

Really interesting and good cocktails. Bartenders know what they are doing here. Well done room - good place for conversation or hanging with friends. My go-to spot for a pre or post dinner drink. Always good on date night.  Food is also very tasty but mostly small plates.
Lovely quaint outdoor seating, the food does not match- nothing quaint about it. Sophisticated countryside cuisine. A must eat for Park Slope.
Very good cocktails and small plates to wash them down. The happy hour is also a very good deal and the service has always been attentive if a little slow. A backyard is always a plus too.
Cozy back patio with fun cocktails and delicious charcuterie
Great, reliable cocktail selection. Espresso cocktail is delicious, but warning- it will keep you awake.
Great cocktails

Best cocktail bar in park Slope area. Love ordering bartenders choice. Bartenders make excellent cocktails with very little direction. Often ask for something refreshing and they make something to match. Great tapas options. The bruchetta is so tasty. They have an outdoor space too! Never had to wait long for a table or spot at the bar. Friendly service.
Awesome spot for a date!  Great backyard space.
Sunshine Co's sister restaurant. Not as good food-wise but still packs a great experience.
One of my favorite spots in Park Slope. Am and will always be a regular.
Enjoy a cheese place, anchovies, beer, and spice infused cocktails.
Great little low-key cocktail spot.  Everything is made to perfection and the service is friendly.  Nice dark lighting adds to the atmosphere.
Super amazing cocktails, friendly staff, fabulous ambience! Loved it :-)

Well-situated Park Slope watering hole with high-end cocktails and a loud but comfortable interior. Drinks are average to good, and the prices are fair but not spectacular. Surprisingly good (but limited) draft list too.
I like the blueprint bar it is kind of mellow and perfect for a drink late at night the music and the enviroment are great and the bartenders are amazing...lovely lovely bar
Owner is awesome food/drinks no complaints
Great food, great drinks, great vibe.
A fun bar with a great drink menu and cool ambiance. Killer happy hour specials as well!
Love the place but It's almost impossible to get a seat if you show up after 8pm. If you can get a seat though, they do make great cocktails.
Simply creative awesome  drinks.

While it might billed as a cocktail bar (and the drinks are fabulous), the food blew me away. Yes, the charcuterie and cheese are amazing and work with the bar atmosphere, but once the small plates start coming out, it's hard not to stay for dinner (and dessert). Highlights - Baby Octopus with potatoes and salsa verde, Chocolate Bread Pudding, and the Blood & Sand, their excellent cocktail du jour!
This is the best cocktail bar in Brooklyn, hands down! And the food is fantastic as well!
I loooove the menu... Good plates and nice house cocktails. Ambiance is cosy , right size and warm interior.

Cocktails are what it's all about here. I highly recommend the "Lost in Austin" (tequila, fresh watermelon juice, serrano pepper syrup, lime) or the "Kentucky Waltz" (bourbon, ceylon tea, maple syrup, mint -- basically their take on a mint julep). Brunch options here are pretty limited so be sure to check out the menu before heading in.
One of our favorite neighborhood spots!  Some of the friendliest bartenders in NYC, plus great drinks and food!
Absolutely love this place! Wonderful food and drinks! Really great staff and a beautiful backyard. Definitely recommend this place to all my friends
Favorite bar in New York. Period.

Probably the perfect place to pre-game on a date. If you're waiting on a dinner reservation or for the dance floor at Union Hall to heat up you'll like this cocktail spot. It's pretty fancy, for BK at least, with a very hipster vibe (more so the staff than the customers). They make very good use of the space with numerous seats while being very cozy and not cramped.  Fun cocktail menu. Complex and spicy options abound. Probably the top spot for cocktails in Park Slope. Service can be slow when they're busy so you may have to order from the bar if at a table and want quicker service.  Very small outdoor space with about 3 tables. I always prefer being indoors no matter what the weather is like as the area is just too small with no view, and feels cut off from the energy inside. Only downside to this place is when it gets really busy people like to stand in the aisle between the bar and the tables, which causes traffic jams.

great cocktails and bar selection!  proper bartenders who still know how to make a drink with finesse.  food isn't too bad either (Rabbit pot pie) and still manages to have draft beers in there too.  Update: had the Duck Club Sandwich for brunch a weekend ago, one of the best sandwiches I've had, ever.
Brunch was good. Cocktails are yummy. The proprietor is cool. I like to eat there everytime I come to NY.

i've only been here for brunch, which is amazing...and the wait is never too long.  two words - bloody maria.  i don't even like cocktails of the bloody sort, but an exception is always made for this one...chipotle-infused tequila is seriously a thing of magic.
